'''Kapila Abhayawansa''' PhD, (Sri Lanka) is the Dean of the Faculty of Religious Studies, [[International Buddhist College]], [[Thailand]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ibc.ac.th/en/node/332 |title=Prof. Dr. Kapila Abhayawansa |author= |date=14 February 2011 |work= |publisher=[[International Buddhist College]] |accessdate=14 May 2011}}{{primary source inline|date=February 2017}}</ref>

==Career==
Prior to joining the college, he was a professor and head of the Department of Buddhist Culture at the Postgraduate Institute of Pali and Buddhist Studies, [[University of Kelaniya]], [[Sri Lanka]]. His areas of specialization are the history of Western and Eastern philosophy, [[Mahayana Buddhist]] philosophy, and [[Buddhist monasticism|Buddhist monastic discipline]].

